-- Pimco Total Return Fund April net outflows $3.1 bln -Morningstar 
-- By Jennifer Ablan and Sam Forgione
-- Thu May 01, 2014 04:26PM EDT
-- None



May 1 (Reuters) - Bill Gross's Pimco Total Return Fund had net outflows of $3.1 billion in April, marking the 12th straight month of outflows for the world's largest bond fund, according to Morningstar data on Thursday.

The Pimco Total Return ETF <BOND.P> had net outflows of $75 million in April, marking its 12th straight month of outflows as well, Morningstar data added.